HEADWORD: Sales tax
<hw>Sales" tax</hw> <pr>(s⟦amac⟧lz"t⟦acr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sales</ets> + <ets>tax</ets>.]</ety> <def>a tax imposed upon
the retail sale of goods or the sale of services, usually collected by
the seller at the time of purchase; -- it is typically calculated as a
percentage of the price of the object sold, being commonly from 3% to 7%
of the <er>base price</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saleswoman</ent>⟦br⟧
